name: Paul Noble

experience.title: Lead Developer
experience.description: Led a team of 5 mobile and web developers to deliver and iterate quickly (website can be found at Outlitapp.com). Unfortunately the startup ended up failing as we could not secure funding for us to continue running, but we ended up creating a product we are proud of. I'm still under an NDA for the project so no media relating to the project is available, other than the website.

experience.title: IT College to Corporate Intern
experience.description: Worked in the International Corporate Services (ICS) branch of Vanguard to develope an AWS solution for ingesting and delivering website user data to corporate analysts. AWS technologies used include: AWS Elastic Map Reduce (Using the Hadoop filesystem), AWS EC2, AWS Cloud formation, AWS Buckets, and AWS security rules/profiles

experience.title: IT TLP Intern
experience.description: Worked in a team of interns developing a mechanism of drug delivery for disaster relief scenarios with a remote drone and mobile application. Developed an API with node that interfaced with a mobile and webapp to command a remote drone. Technologies used: React Native and MEAN stack.

education.award: Minor in Entrepreneurship and New Venture Growth

projects.title: EduSmart
projects.description: Enterprise javaFX program made to help special education teachers track students behavior in the classroom. Project deployed and delivered to over 12 different special education schools in Virginia affecting 100s of educators. Integrates with these school systems existing projects. Licensed to Centra health and more to come.

projects.title: StockHelper
projects.description: This project is in its early stages. We are working on developing a mobile application for iOS and Android to teach people about stocks and stock trading. We are targeting users he may not do much of their own research or don't know where to start with their research. We are in the ideation and design phase currently.

bio: Hi my name is Paul Noble and I am a current Computer Science student at Virginia Tech also pursuing a minors in Entrepreneurship and New Venture Growth and Math. I am interested in entrepreneurship, mobile developement, and data science.
